    "The PIL's sophisticated probabilistic calculations require robust computational resources, particularly in terms of processing power and memory.",
    "The experimental setup utilized high-end GPUs and a powerful CPU to handle these demands.",
    "However, such hardware may not be readily accessible in all research or practical settings, potentially limiting the wider adoption of this enhanced LLM technology.",
    "This hardware dependency highlights a need for optimization strategies that could make the PIL more feasible on a broader range of computational platforms, including those with more modest specifications.Another limitation concerns the issue of biases inherent in LLMs.",
